caption.text:
Sneaker Week [3/3]

Adidas YEEZY Boost 350 "Pirate Black":
A low-top sneaker designed by Kanye West. This shoe was considered the best sneaker of 2015 by various sneakerhead forums. The shoes first debut at the YEEZY season fashion show in February. The woven one-piece upper is fantastically constructed, and the Boost sole is vastly superior to that of a shoe like the Roshe One. This particular colorway is the only one that got restock recently. #boostvibes #yeezyboost350 #hypefeet

Sneaker Week [2/3]

Air Jordan 7 Retro "Barcelona Nights":
Initially thought to usher in the Looney Tunes reference with a Marvin the Martian nod, because the accents on this sneaker match  the alien's style choices. Actually this shoe takes Mike back to 1992 Olympics with a vibrant choice of Blue Graphite, Retro, and infrared 23 to represent the Spanish city's exuberant night life. Featuring a muted base that sports a premium construction of black nubuck and leather, this only enhances the accents on the outsole and throughout.

Sneaker Week [1/3]

Adidas Consortium Tubular Runner:
The first model of the Tubular series. Heavily inspired by Y-3 Qasa, this sneaker gained a strong fan base in recent months. As a part of Adidas Consortium collection the Tubular Runner presented in black and white versions, featuring fully tonal uppers with premium leather accents and white outer soles.
